# Luna Agent Kit

- Read **`docs/workflows/WORKFLOW.md`** for the phase menu (frontmatter phases, gates,
  `suggested_skills`, `variants`). Pick 0..N skills from the current phase; skills are **independent**
  (none chains into another).
- Follow **`AGENTS.md`** — the shared entry for both Cursor and Claude Code.
- Plans live in `docs/plans/`, specs in `docs/specs/`, backlog in `docs/TODO.md`, registry in
  `docs/PLANS.md`. A plan is **self-contained** (tasks + acceptance) so you can implement it without
  the other tool.
- Commit with a `Plan: docs/plans/<file>.md#phase-N` trailer during plan work; update the plan's
  `PLANS.md` row (set **Owner** to the active tool).
- When the user corrects you, append a one-liner to **`.cursor/rules/lessons.mdc`** (and mirror to
  `.claude/rules/lessons.md`).
